  "text": "The gRPC health check protocol compliance in envoyproxy/envoy is implemented primarily through the gRPC health checker extension located in source/extensions/health_checkers/grpc/. The implementation follows the grpc.health.v1.Health service specification as defined in the gRPC proto (github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/master/src/proto/grpc/health/v1/health.proto).\n\nKey implementation details:\n\n1. **Service Implementation**: The GrpcHealthCheckerFactory (source/extensions/health_checkers/grpc/health_checker_impl.h) creates instances of GrpcHealthCheckerImpl, which implements the Upstream::HealthChecker interface. The service method is resolved at initialization (line 63-64 in health_checker_impl.cc) using the method descriptor for \"grpc.health.v1.Health.Check\".\n\n2. **HealthCheckRequest Handling**: The HealthCheckRequest message is constructed in the onInterval() method (line 233 in health_checker_impl.cc). The service name is optionally populated from the GrpcHealthCheck configuration (line 234-236).\n\n3. **HealthCheckResponse Parsing**: The HealthCheckResponse is parsed from the gRPC response in the decodeData() method (line 151 in health_checker_impl.cc) using the grpc::health::v1::HealthCheckResponse protocol buffer message.\n\n4. **Health Status Response Mapping**: The response status values are mapped as follows (lines 307, 372-387 in health_checker_impl.cc):\n   - SERVING (value 1): Maps to host health success\n   - NOT_SERVING (value 2): Maps to host health failure\n   - UNKNOWN (value 0): Maps to host health failure\n   - SERVICE_UNKNOWN (value 3): Maps to host health failure\n\n5. **Protocol Compliance**: The implementation handles HTTP/2 frame decoding (Grpc::Decoder at line 120), gRPC trailers with status codes, and proper HTTP status mapping to gRPC status codes (lines 96-128 in decodeHeaders). The implementation also follows the gRPC health checking specification for handling the unary Check RPC method (comment at line 147).\n\n6. **Supporting Infrastructure**: The health discovery service (source/common/upstream/health_discovery_service.h/cc) provides HDS (Health Discovery Service) integration. The base health checker implementation (source/common/upstream/health_checker_impl.h/cc) includes the grpc health proto dependency and provides the factory and registration mechanism for the gRPC health checker.\n\nThe implementation in envoy--v1.31.2 at source/extensions/health_checkers/grpc/ provides a complete, standards-compliant implementation of the grpc.health.v1.Health service Check RPC method for active health checking of gRPC services."
}

